@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Before using these examples, run: node src/demoReceiver.js (in another terminal)
### 2. Successful delivery
# Copy the returned delivery.id into @deliveryId below, then use request 5.
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "http://localhost:4000/success",
  "payload": { "event": "payment.succeeded", "paymentId": "pay_123" },
  "headers": { "x-webhook-source": "smart-retry-queue-demo" }
}

### 3. Retry then success demo: this local receiver returns 503 twice, then 200
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "http://localhost:4000/flaky",
  "payload": { "event": "invoice.created", "invoiceId": "inv_456" },
  "headers": {}
}

### 4. Dead-letter demo: returns 500 and becomes DEAD after five attempts.
# To demonstrate quickly, start main app with BACKOFF_DELAYS_MS=1000,1000,1000,1000,1000 npm start.
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "http://localhost:4000/fail",
  "payload": { "event": "customer.deleted" },
  "headers": {}
}

### 5. Permanent failure demo: 410 becomes DEAD after one attempt
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "http://localhost:4000/gone",
  "payload": { "event": "customer.deleted" },
  "headers": {}
}

### Set this after sending one of the requests above
@deliveryId = REPLACE_WITH_DELIVERY_UUID

### 6. Inspect delivery status and its persistent attempt log
GET {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/{{deliveryId}}

### 7. List all dead-letter deliveries
GET {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/dead

### 8. Replay a DEAD delivery. It resets to PENDING and the worker picks it up.
POST {{baseUrl}}/webhooks/{{deliveryId}}/replay
